A N A C T
RELATING TO COURTS AND CIVIL PROCEDURE -- PROCEDURE GENERALLY -- FEES
Introduced By: Senator Frank A. Ciccone
Date Introduced: February 26, 2025
Referred To: Senate Judiciary
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 9-29-9 of the General Laws in Chapter 9-29 entitled "Fees" is hereby
2 amended to read as follows:
3 9-29-9. Fees of sheriffs, sergeants, and constables.
4 (a) The fees, including mileage, of deputy sheriffs, town sergeants, and constables, for
5 which a deposit to insure payment may be required, shall not exceed the following:
6 (1) For serving any writ of replevin, or out of state papers .................................. $100.00
7 (2) For serving all other writs, citations, or subpoenas ............................... $45.00 $70.00
8 (3) For a writ copy of every one hundred words ....................................................... $2.00
9 (4) For every writ returned when the defendant cannot be found ........................... $15.00
10 (5) For serving any writ of arrest or body attachment .......................................... $100.00
11 (b) The above fees shall be deposited as general revenue.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
